items.name: Predictive-Modeling-using-Logistic-Regression-A-Data-Driven-Approach-to-Classification
items.description: A project showcasing the development and deployment of a Logistic Regression model using Scikit-Learn. The model is converted to ONNX format for cross-platform deployment, ensuring efficient and reliable predictions. Includes data preprocessing, model training, and validation steps with a focus on production readiness.

items.name: Arrhythmia-Classification-Using-Machine-Learning
items.description: This project classifies arrhythmia using the UCI dataset with 279 features and 452 examples. It predicts if a person has arrhythmia and classifies it into 12 types. The notebook includes data preprocessing, feature selection, and machine learning model implementation for accurate medical data prediction.
